> Everything tastes better when cheese is involved, and chicken is no exception. In this recipe, melted Parmesan forms a crispy and super simple crust. We would say it's the star of the show, but the combination of roasted sweet potatoes, peppery arugula, and tart cranberries is hard to beat.

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Cut @sweet potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch cubes (no need to peel them). Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast ~{12%minutes}, toss, then finish roasting until golden brown, another ~{12-13%minutes}.

Mix @panko breadcrumbs{½%cup}, @Parmesan cheese{¼%cup}, and a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a #small bowl{}. Place @chicken breasts{12%ounce} on a lightly oiled baking sheet, and season all over with salt and pepper. Spread top of each chicken breast with a thin layer of @sour cream{1%tablespoon}. Press panko mixture into sour cream to adhere. Add to baking sheet with potatoes, and bake until crust turns golden and chicken is no longer pink in middle, about ~{20%minutes}.

Prep remaining ingredients: Meanwhile, halve, peel, and dice @shallot{1}. Halve @lemon{1}.

Heat @butter{1%tablespoon} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add shallots and toss until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add @chicken stock concentrate{1} and @water{½%cup}. Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add a squeeze of lemon, and season with salt and pepper. Remove pan from heat.

Toss roasted sweet potatoes in a #large bowl{} with @arugula{2%ounce}, @dried cranberries{1%ounce}, @pecans{1%ounce}, a squeeze of lemon, and a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}. Season with salt and pepper.

Serve: Drizzle chicken with pan sauce, serve alongside salad, and enjoy!